This is in excellent condition with orange front Trijicon HD night sights, three 15-rd magazines, an amazingly sweet Double Action/single action trigger with decocker and paddle magazine release. 4" Barrel with Polymer Frame. Easily one of the most comfortable grips on the market. 

Also comes with adjustable backstraps, manual, box, and fobus paddle holster. 

the P99 AS combines the advantages of the traditional Double Action System with Single Action Anti-Stress trigger. The P99 provides the shooter with a user-friendliness previously found only in hammer fired pistols.Traditional Double Action - The anti-stress trigger makes the P99 one of the world's safest firearms by preventing unintentional "reflex" firing in stressful situations. The decisive innovation: When the slide is racked completely to the rear upon loading, the trigger remains in the forward position for the first shot; not only in the double action trigger mode, but also in the single action mode. The P99 AS is equipped with a decocking button to safely decock the striker. 

The trigger reset on this is amazing. Simply put, this is a great handgun.

postcontent:
Up for sale or trade I have an FS2000, this is the Tactical version. Which means it has the rail front end instead of the "guppy" front end.
 I am not the original owner, so the round count is unknown.
 I have shot this rifle and it runs like a champ, no malfunctions what so ever. I only shoot brass cased ammo through my expensive rifles.
 It does have minor marks on the rail where accessories had been attached, if you put on your own accessories you will not see the marks. Or if you paint or coat your gear, it's a non-issue.

 The previous owner did remove the "wipes" inside the mag well, now the mags will drop free, it did not hinder function at all, I just wanted to mention it, so that there are no surprises.
 Speaking of mags, if you are not familiar with the FS2000, it will only accept G.I. mags, this was not a deal breaker for me, but may be for some.

 If you are reading this ad, you probably know that these are no longer being made, I don't see them come up very often on the used market, but they do from time to time.

 Originally I was going to try and chase down all the factory accessories, it does have the factory mag, in addition to that I did manage to find an original cleaning kit with all the small tools including the sight adjustment tool and take down tools. The cleaning/tool kit is complete and the factory kit.

This is FTF in Indy, I may roll for the right deal.
Please be 18yrs or older, with a valid IN DL and a LTCH (carry permit) would be nice, but not a deal breaker.
NO INFO recorded.
I will not respond to emails, asking the following:
Is it still available? The answer is YES, if the ad is up, then yes I still have it.
Will you take my non running project car, tattoo work or airplane rides?
The answer is NO. I will not respond to silly trade offers.
The trades listed are what I'm after, I look on here daily, if I see something I don't have listed and I want it, I will shoot that person an email.

I have an excellent condition progressive shotshell loader, it is the best one out there for loading mass quantities of shotshells, I have tried them all and this one does it all better than the rest. The Grand is designed for the shotgunner who demands precision shotshells. Start a hull at station 1 and insert a wad in the wad guide at station 4. All other functions are performed automatically. Once in full operation, a loaded shotshell is dispensed each time the handle is cycled through the full down and up strokes. The case-activated Powder System means that if there’s no hull in place, no powder is dropped, preventing spillage and eliminating the need to manually turn the powder on and off.
 Front-mounted powder charging station makes it easy to view the powder charge and remove the charged hull for weighing, if necessary
• Powder System provides three positions for the Powder Measure: on, off and empty
• Powder Bushings interchange in about 30 seconds and are available for all popular loads
• Powder Hopper holds up to 1 pound of smokeless powder
• Case-activated shot system prevents spillage and is easily drained
• Shot Bushings interchange in about 30 seconds, and are available for most popular charge weights and shot sizes
• Shot Hopper capacity is 25 pounds 
• Conversion Kits are available for changing to 12- or 20-gauge as required
